- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method for low-rank decomposition of incomplete tensors, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method has applications in recommender systems, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The proposed method can be applied to image inpainting, which is a common problem in computer vision. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the computational complexity of the proposed method and adapts a fast iterative shrinkage-thresholding technique to reduce it. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a penalty functional to place structural sparsity over the core tensor, which can be seen as a form of data compression and has connections to information theory.
